snippet: Stocks slipped at the start of trading, despite an unexpectedly strong increase in consumer spending last month.
abstract: Stocks rise slightly, lifting the Dow Jones industrial average to its ninth consecutive gain, its longest winning streak in more than 16 years.
lead_paragraph: Stocks slipped at the start of trading, despite an unexpectedly strong increase in consumer spending last month.
